        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files</note>
                <head>No. 1333<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Chief of
                        Staff, United States Army</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MGAGC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marshall</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1333fn1">Printed from the text relayed by
                            <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> to the <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Department in telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                        </gloss> 370 of July 27, where it is described as a “memorandum for
                            <persName corresp="#p_MGAGC1">General Marshall</persName> signed by the
                        President under date July 27”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-27">July 27,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to your request for information in regard to the tripartite agreement
                    that “troops of the three powers should be withdrawn from Teheran at once”, you
                    are informed that it is my desire that United States troops be withdrawn from
                    Teheran within 60 days if it is practicable to do so.</p>
                <p>It is not intended that the <persName corresp="#p_RMGCS1">Ridley</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLCHN1">Schwarzkopf</persName> missions and that
                        <gloss target="#t_ATC1">A. T. C.</gloss> personnel and facilities in Iran be
                    withdrawn at the present time.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
